BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:arts-council-wales-creative-steps-individuals-2026@artificialnouveau.gi
 thub.io
DTSTAMP:20260707T125543Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260729
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260730
SUMMARY:Deadline: Creative Steps for Individuals 2026 (Arts Council of Wale
 s)
DESCRIPTION:Creative Steps funds the professional\, business and organisati
 onal development of artists who have experienced barriers to careers withi
 n the arts. Creative Steps for Individuals is open to individual artists a
 nd creatives who identify as being Ethnically and Culturally diverse\, D/d
 eaf\, disabled or neurodivergent\, groups that are underrepresented in Art
 s Council of Wales funding programmes due to barriers to entry. Applicants
  must have demonstrable experience as an artist or creative professional\;
  those without may still be supported on the basis of artistic potential b
 y submitting a portfolio\, CV or examples of work\, discussed with a Relat
 ionship Manager. WHAT IT SUPPORTS: career development\, NOT creating new w
 ork or project delivery. Examples include peer-to-peer learning\, training
  courses (not formal/vocational education)\, building networks\, mentorshi
 p/coaching\, business development/social media/marketing advice\, website 
 development/marketing materials/equipment or materials\, and setting up a 
 new organisation. Budgets may include the applicant's own time\, freelance
 r costs (paid at standard industry rates)\, mentor/consultant costs\, acce
 ss costs\, and childcare/caregiving costs. AMOUNT: GBP 500 to GBP 7\,500 (
 plus access costs)\; up to 90% of the developmental cost\, with the remain
 ing 10% from a non-Arts Council of Wales / non-National Lottery source (in
 -kind\, cash\, or both\, confirmed by letters of support). No application 
 fee. APPLY: applicants must express interest at least 3 weeks before the d
 eadline to receive support from an Application Coach or Access Support coo
 rdinator\; an application form is provided by a Relationship Manager. The 
 fund runs in rounds\; the next round (Round 2 2026) has an Expression of I
 nterest cut-off of 8 July 2026 and an application deadline of 29 July 2026
 . Later rounds: Round 3 (EOI 30 September\, deadline 21 October 2026) and 
 Round 4 (EOI 10 February\, deadline 3 March 2027).\n\nOrganisation: Arts C
 ouncil of Wales\nLocation: Wales\, United Kingdom. For artists and creativ
 es based in Wales.\nAward: GBP 500 to GBP 7\,500 (plus access costs). Appl
 icants can apply for up to 90% of the developmental cost\; the remaining 1
 0% must come from a non-Arts Council of Wales / non-National Lottery sourc
 e (in-kind\, cash\, or both).\nDuration: Supports a stage of professional 
 development\; allow a minimum of 10 working weeks between the deadline and
  the project start date.\n\nMore: http://arts.wales/funding/individuals/cr
 eative-steps-for-individuals
URL:http://arts.wales/funding/individuals/creative-steps-for-individuals
LOCATION:Wales\, United Kingdom. For artists and creatives based in Wales.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:siap-major-individual-artists-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260707T125543Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260720
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260721
SUMMARY:Deadline: SIAP: Major Individual Artists Award 2026/27 (Arts Counci
 l NI)
DESCRIPTION:The Major Individual Artists award\, part of Arts Council NI's 
 National Lottery Support for Individual Artists Programme (SIAP)\, funds e
 xtended or ambitious work by established artists\, covering specific proje
 cts\, specialised research\, personal artistic development\, and materials
 /equipment. AMOUNT: four awards of up to GBP 15\,000 each in 2026/27. ELIG
 IBILITY: established artists across all disciplines with national/internat
 ional recognition who have not previously received a major award\; academi
 cs and postgraduate artists are eligible if the project costs do not relat
 e to their institutional work or studies. Applicants must contact the rele
 vant artform officer before submission (by 10 July 2026)\; applications wi
 thout this prior contact are ineligible. No application fee. The online ap
 plication system closes precisely at the deadline and applicants must rece
 ive a confirmation email to verify successful submission. Deadline: Monday
  20 July 2026\, 12:00 noon.\n\nOrganisation: Arts Council of Northern Irel
 and\nLocation: Northern Ireland\, United Kingdom. Applicants must be based
  in Northern Ireland.\nAward: Up to GBP 15\,000 per award\; four awards av
 ailable in 2026/27. Funded through the National Lottery Support for Indivi
 dual Artists Programme (SIAP).\nDuration: Supports specific projects\, spe
 cialised research\, personal artistic development and materials/equipment.
  Activity duration not specified.\n\nMore: https://artscouncil-ni.org/fund
 ing-for-individuals/major-individual-artists
URL:https://artscouncil-ni.org/funding-for-individuals/major-individual-art
 ists
LOCATION:Northern Ireland\, United Kingdom. Applicants must be based in Nor
 thern Ireland.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:siap-project-funding-individuals-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260707T125543Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260730
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260731
SUMMARY:Deadline: SIAP: Project Funding for Individual Artists 2026 (Arts C
 ouncil NI)
DESCRIPTION:Project Funding for Individuals\, part of Arts Council NI's Nat
 ional Lottery Support for Individual Artists Programme (SIAP)\, funds proj
 ect-based creative activities across all artistic disciplines. Eligible ac
 tivities include creating new work\, research and development\, residencie
 s\, mentoring\, professional development\, and time dedicated to specific 
 creative outcomes. ELIGIBLE COSTS: art materials\, artist fees/time\, resi
 dency costs\, travel (mileage at GBP 0.257/mile)\, venue hire\, technical 
 equipment (max 50% of request value)\, and IT equipment (laptops/PCs up to
  GBP 1\,200\; tablets up to GBP 500). ELIGIBILITY: artists of all discipli
 nes and career stages\, including emerging artists (less than 5 years prof
 essional experience)\, and in some cases technical staff/administrators\; 
 students and academics at third-level institutions may apply with departme
 ntal approval showing the costs are not covered by their employer or acade
 mic work. AMOUNT: GBP 62 to GBP 15\,000. No application fee. Deadline: Thu
 rsday 30 July 2026\, 12:00 noon (online submission required).\n\nOrganisat
 ion: Arts Council of Northern Ireland\nLocation: Northern Ireland\, United
  Kingdom. Applicants must be based in Northern Ireland.\nAward: GBP 62 to 
 GBP 15\,000. Funded through the National Lottery Support for Individual Ar
 tists Programme (SIAP).\nDuration: Project-based activity\; duration not s
 pecified.\n\nMore: https://artscouncil-ni.org/funding-for-individuals/proj
 ect-funding-for-individuals
URL:https://artscouncil-ni.org/funding-for-individuals/project-funding-for-
 individuals
LOCATION:Northern Ireland\, United Kingdom. Applicants must be based in Nor
 thern Ireland.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:siap-artists-international-development-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.gith
 ub.io
DTSTAMP:20260707T125543Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260730
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260731
SUMMARY:Deadline: SIAP: Artists' International Development Fund 2026 (Arts 
 Council NI)
DESCRIPTION:The Artists' International Development Fund (AIDF)\, part of Ar
 ts Council NI's National Lottery Support for Individual Artists Programme 
 (SIAP)\, funds early-stage international development opportunities for ind
 ividual\, freelance and self-employed artists to build networks abroad. EL
 IGIBLE COSTS: art materials\, travel\, residencies (up to 4 weeks)\, techn
 ical fees\, venue hire\, and equipment\, with IT devices capped at GBP 1\,
 200 for laptops/PCs and GBP 500 for tablets. ELIGIBILITY: artists across a
 ll disciplines\, particularly emerging artists (under 5 years professional
  experience)\; academics and students at third-level institutions may appl
 y if the project differs from their employment/studies. AIDF applicants mu
 st have received recognition for their work in Northern Ireland\, lack ext
 ensive international experience\, and demonstrate interest in their work f
 rom an overseas partner/host. AMOUNT: GBP 62 to GBP 15\,000. No applicatio
 n fee. Deadline: Thursday 30 July 2026\, 12:00 noon.\n\nOrganisation: Arts
  Council of Northern Ireland\nLocation: Northern Ireland\, United Kingdom.
  Applicants must be based in Northern Ireland\; international development 
 takes place abroad with overseas partners/hosts.\nAward: GBP 62 to GBP 15\
 ,000. Funded through the National Lottery Support for Individual Artists P
 rogramme (SIAP).\nDuration: Early-stage international development opportun
 ities\; residencies supported for a maximum of 4 weeks.\n\nMore: https://a
 rtscouncil-ni.org/funding-for-individuals/artists-international-developmen
 t-fund-individuals
URL:https://artscouncil-ni.org/funding-for-individuals/artists-internationa
 l-development-fund-individuals
LOCATION:Northern Ireland\, United Kingdom. Applicants must be based in Nor
 thern Ireland\; international development takes place abroad with overseas
  partners/hosts.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:restless-egg-batch-2-luxury-technology-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260707T125543Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260717
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260718
SUMMARY:Deadline: Restless Egg: Batch 2\, Luxury Technology (Accelerator fo
 r Artist-Founders) 2026
DESCRIPTION:Restless Egg is a London-based incubator for "artist-founders"\
 , an emerging genre of creative people whose work sits between art\, techn
 ology and building commercial products. It invests in creative founders an
 d runs a six-month\, high-touch accelerator program to help them build com
 mercially successful and scalable companies at the bleeding edge of cultur
 e and technology. BATCH 2 (LUXURY TECHNOLOGY) is open for applications\, s
 eeking founders building luxury technologies: commercial products that use
  AI and other emerging technologies to unlock richer\, stranger\, more mea
 ningful forms of human experience\, not just more efficiency. For this bat
 ch Restless Egg has doubled its initial investment to USD 100\,000 for 5% 
 equity\, and increased its follow-on investment to up to USD 175\,000\, ai
 ming to give founders more runway\, more support and more room to build th
 e most ambitious companies. The program supports rapid learning\, sharper 
 product and narrative development\, and real investability through close e
 ngagement with Restless Egg and its network of subject-matter experts\, co
 llaborators\, operators and investors\; the follow-on is released when pre
 defined performance metrics are met. NOTE: this is a dilutive equity inves
 tment (it takes a 5% stake)\, not a non-dilutive grant or fellowship. Appl
 ications are open (no fixed deadline stated). Apply at https://apply.restl
 essegg.com.\n\nOrganisation: Restless Egg\nLocation: London-based incubato
 r (UK)\; open to creative "artist-founders" internationally\, with in-pers
 on gatherings (a first-batch salon was held at Sybil in Berlin).\nAward: E
 quity-based investment (NOT a non-dilutive grant): USD 100\,000 initial in
 vestment for 5% equity\, plus up to USD 175\,000 in follow-on investment w
 hen predefined performance metrics are met. Includes a high-touch accelera
 tor program and access to a network of subject-matter experts\, collaborat
 ors\, operators and investors.\nDuration: Six-month accelerator program\n\
 nMore: https://apply.restlessegg.com
URL:https://apply.restlessegg.com
LOCATION:London-based incubator (UK)\; open to creative "artist-founders" i
 nternationally\, with in-person gatherings (a first-batch salon was held a
 t Sybil in Berlin).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:future-observatory-prototype-grants-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260707T125543Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260612
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260613
SUMMARY:Deadline: Future Observatory: Prototype Grants 2026 (Sustainable Su
 pply Chains)
DESCRIPTION:Four grants of up to GBP 70\,000 from Future Observatory (the D
 esign Museum's national design research programme) and the AHRC\, awarded 
 to UK architecture and design practices for prototype development and seco
 nd-stage design research in more sustainable supply chains. Open to small-
 to-medium sized practices across all architecture and design disciplines\,
  including fashion\, product design\, material research\, systems thinking
  and interdisciplinary practices. Proposals should focus on sustainable su
 pply chains\, with particular interest in bioregional\, biomaterial and re
 generative approaches\; relevant themes include retrofit\, regenerative ma
 terials and systems\, circular design\, waste reduction and reuse\, low-ca
 rbon housing\, agricultural byproducts\, and data-led tools and approaches
 . ELIGIBILITY: UK-based small-to-medium architecture and design practices.
  Opens 6 May 2026\, 10:00am\; closes 12 June 2026\, 4:00pm.\n\nOrganisatio
 n: Future Observatory and AHRC\nLocation: United Kingdom\nAward: Up to GBP
  70\,000 per grant (four grants available\; award range GBP 60\,000-70\,00
 0). Total fund GBP 300\,000. No application fee.\nDuration: Prototype deve
 lopment and second-stage design research\n\nMore: https://futureobservator
 y.org/research/apply-for-funding/prototype-grants
URL:https://futureobservatory.org/research/apply-for-funding/prototype-gran
 ts
LOCATION:United Kingdom
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
